        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "MiMo: Safari + Chrome auto import; fix Chrome-only copy elsewhere",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nCloses #1304.\n\n**MiMo Auto browser policy (ClawSweeper P1 addressed in `041b2c3e`):**\n- Replace main’s Chrome-only list with `ProviderBrowserCookieDefaults.mimoCookieImportOrder = [.safari, .chrome, .chromeBeta, .chromeCanary]`.\n- Keep Firefox / Edge / other Chromium forks on **Manual** import to match `AGENTS.md` prompt guidance.\n- Align settings subtitle, 11 locale strings, and `docs/mimo.md` with that curated order.\n\n**Sibling Chrome-only copy fixes:**\n- **Mistral**: stop defaulting cookie import to `[.chrome]` only.\n- **Command Code / Alibaba Token Plan**: use each provider’s `browserCookieOrder.loginHint` instead of hardcoded “sign in in Chrome”.\n- **Docs**: `ollama.md`, `alibaba-token-plan.md`, `augment.md`.\n\n## Evidence / proof\n\n### 1. Source inspection — before vs after (MiMo Auto order)\n\n**Before (`origin/main`):** MiMo descriptor hard-coded Chrome only.\n\n```swift\nlet browserOrder: BrowserCookieImportOrder = [\n    .chrome,\n    .chromeBeta,\n    .chromeCanary,\n]\n```\n\n**After (`041b2c3e`):** explicit curated order in `ProviderBrowserCookieDefaults.mimoCookieImportOrder`:\n\n```swift\n[.safari, .chrome, .chromeBeta, .chromeCanary]\n```\n\nWiring: `MiMoProviderDescriptor` → `browserCookieOrder: ProviderBrowserCookieDefaults.mimoCookieImportOrder` → `MiMoCookieImporter` reads `ProviderDefaults.metadata[.mimo]?.browserCookieOrder`.\n\n### 2. Regression tests — browser scope pinned\n\n`swift test --filter \"BrowserCookieOrderStatusStringTests|MiMoProviderTests\"` on macOS (`041b2c3e`):\n\n```\n✔ Test \"mimo cookie import order puts safari ahead of chrome variants\" passed\n✔ Test \"mimo web strategy retries imported sessions after decode failure\" passed\n✔ Test \"mimo importer merges profile stores before validating auth cookies\" passed\n✔ Test \"mistral automatic cookies use provider browser order\" passed\n✔ Test \"command code missing credentials includes browser login hint\" passed\n✔ Test \"alibaba token plan missing cookie includes browser login hint\" passed\n✔ Test run with 31 tests in 2 suites passed after 0.045 seconds\n```\n\nNegative assertions in `BrowserCookieOrderStatusStringTests`:\n- `#expect(!order.contains(.firefox))`\n- `#expect(!order.contains(.edge))`\n\n### 3. End-to-end import path (stubbed, no Keychain prompts)\n\n`MiMoProviderTests` → `mimo web strategy retries imported sessions after decode failure` exercises the Auto import → balance fetch path using injected browser sessions (`sourceLabel: \"Active Chrome\"`) and verifies balance rendering (`Balance: $25.51`). This proves the web strategy consumes imported cookie sessions after the browser-order change without requiring live Keychain access.\n\n### 4. Why no live Safari/Chrome screenshot\n\nPer `AGENTS.md`, live browser-cookie import can trigger macOS Keychain / Full Disk Access prompts, so validation here uses focused XCTest coverage plus source inspection instead of a live signed-in browser capture. Happy to add a redacted maintainer screenshot if someone can run the build locally with a MiMo session in Safari or Chrome.\n\n## Commands run\n\n- `swift test --filter \"BrowserCookieOrderStatusStringTests|MiMoProviderTests\"` — 31 tests pass\n- `make check` — 0 violations across 1017 files\n\n## Intentionally unchanged\n\n- **Grok** and **OpenCode** (non-Go) remain Chrome-only by design.\n- **Ollama / Abacus** remain Chrome-first with fallback; only misleading docs were updated.",
